16/06/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu called for regular briefings Wednesday (15 June) from the Central Election Commission (CEC) about preparations for the 3 July parliamentary vote. During a meeting with CEC Chairman Ilirjan Celibashi, Moisiu also requested guidance about any specific problems that emerge in the process. The vote is considered crucial to Albania's democratic development and its bid for Euro-Atlantic integration. (Albanian News - 16/06/05; Albanian President's Web site - 15/06/05)
